# Code Quality

- Prefer small, focused changes that match existing patterns.
- Keep TypeScript strictness and avoid `any` unless justified.
- Preserve user-visible behavior unless task explicitly requires changes.
- Add/update docs when behavior or workflow changes.
- Do not commit or expose secrets; use env vars and `env.example`.
- Validate with available checks (`build`, `lint`, targeted runtime checks) before declaring completion.
